race.comment: YOU SEE ME (6) hit the ground running and was prominent to the turn but faded out of it when 7th at this track in Grade 6 company. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Should bounce back. CANYA BELIEVE IT (4) finds it hard to break through. Finished second (23.30) at this track last time making it three minors on end. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Likely to be in the finish again. COLOUR OF RED (2) was in traffic and missed the frame in a Grade 5 at this track over 300m latest, finishing a 4 length fifth (17.59). Has Box 2 this time where he has a win. Should be in this for a long way. GETTIN' TIPSY (1) can find the frame without surprising. Something for the Multiples: CHEERS COBBER (5) HOLLYWOOD MISS (3)
